    <p class="bk-notes en">
      Wang Yangming’s philosophy begins with a reversal: what if principle is not something to be sought in the world, but something that already resides within the mind? “The mind is principle” does not expand the world — it removes all distance. The question is no longer where truth lies, but whether we are willing to recognize it in ourselves.
    </p>
    
    <p class="bk-notes zh" style="display:none">
      王阳明的思想从一种“反转”开始：理，并不在万物之中等待被寻找，而早已存在于心。“心即理”并没有扩展世界，反而取消了一切距离。问题不再是理在何处，而在于我们是否愿意在自身之中承认它。
    </p>

